  ---
  A few notes:
  - Kyber and Dilithium are dual/triple-licensed — you can choose the most permissive option (Public Domain) for most use cases.
  - XKCP is predominantly CC0 but has narrow BSD 3-Clause carve-outs for two files; worth calling out explicitly if doing a formal license audit.
  - libcpucycles appears to be a benchmarking/development dependency only and likely doesn't need to be included in a production license notice.
  
  
  